  * Make the slideshow feature respect the preferences zoom quality setting instead of always being low (#83)

  [ Michael Webster ]
  * print settings: Remove 'pixel' option in units selector. It is confusing because it's treated *exactly* the same as millimeters, and doesn't make much sense as a physical unit of measure even if it was properly calculated.
  * print settings: Keep images centered until explicitly moved off center (or Custom is explicitly selected).  It makes no sense to have the center combobox revert to Custom when adjusting the image size.
  * gth-image-print-job.c: Update spin button settings when the view is first created, not just when the units combobox is changed.
  * gth-image-print-job.c: Use better spinbutton settings, and allow adjustment to two decimal places when inch units are selected.
  * various: check for valid surfaces after creating them.

  [ icarter09 ]
  * Added line on how to remove image from selection

